{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place frozen banana into mixing bowl and blend <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Add peanut butter and coconut milk and blend <b>40 sec\/speed 6<b>, until almost smooth.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then blend <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>, until smooth.","If ice cream is too soft, transfer into a freezable container and place into freezer until firm. Drizzle with coconut nectar (optional) and sprinkle with cacao nibs (optional) and toasted coconut flakes to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["250 g banana, cut into pieces and frozen","100 g smooth peanut butter","100 g coconut milk","coconut nectar, to serve (optional - see Tips)","cacao nibs, to serve (optional - see Tips)","coconut flakes, toasted, to serve"]}],"id":"r391307","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-IA6iS8tVfn0\/XZWZXjKqP2I\/AAAAAAAAeL0\/7wd_OvTffK0nJ4jF1gwpkI6LBWgPFx5hwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_a90JtszrHghMBBYp.png","title":"Peanut butter banana ice cream","publishedAt":"2019-05-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13.6 g","fat":"33.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"32.6 g","calories":"2058.8 kJ \/ 490.2 kcal"},"usefulItems":"freezable container, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Baby's serve<\/strong>: many babies do not like very cold foods, so you may wish to wait until your baby is happily accepting cold foods before offering this ice cream. Omit coconut nectar (which is a form of sugar) and cacao nibs (which contain caffeine) and cut up coconut flakes.","<strong>Toddler's serve<\/strong>: omit or reduce coconut nectar (which is a form of sugar) and cacao nibs (which contain caffeine).","Be sure to use pure peanut butter made from 100 per cent nuts and free from refined oils and added sugar. You can also make your own peanut butter in your Thermomix - you'll find the recipes on Cookidoo.","When buying coconut flakes, try to choose brands with no added sulphur dioxide. Organic brands are generally sulphur-free. Sulphur dioxide (220) is a preservative that's been associated with a range of food intolerance symptoms and can particularly affect asthma sufferers.","This recipe can be doubled."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","10m","2 portions"]}